modules.description: Handles WebSocket connections by processing incoming data streams and managing connection state. It provides an input handler for integrating with HTTP servers that upgrade connections to WebSockets. This module works with `Stream.stream` and `Httpun_ws.Websocket_connection.input_handlers` to facilitate bidirectional communication over WebSockets.

This module enables WebSocket communication by processing data streams and managing connection state during HTTP upgrades. It integrates with HTTP servers to handle bidirectional messaging using `Stream.stream` and `Httpun_ws.Websocket_connection.input_handlers`. Developers can use it to implement real-time features like chat services or live updates by sending and receiving WebSocket messages. Example use cases include handling client-server interactions over persistent connections and managing message routing within an HTTP framework.
